[thinking] **Considering build configuration**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I don't need any tests right now, but I think I should keep coverage classes in their own files. Maybe I need to package something outside the library, like com_diffplug. I have a potential issue with the build.gradle fixture regarding Java source for the DiktatFormatterFunc class.
[thinking] 
[thinking] Additionally, I'm pondering the necessity of including the @Override annotation. Maybe I should add it for clarity, even if it doesn't affect the functionality? I'm also looking into dynamic access tracking. It seems like external jar classes can't be loaded dynamically in native images. I should check if existing fixtures follow this pattern.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Analyzing dynamic class loading**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm realizing that Native Image doesn't allow dynamic class loading from new jars at runtime. But in my tests, it seems fixture jars are included as resources, which are extracted at runtime. I wonder how existing tests can pass despite this limitation? Perhaps agent configuration registers classes and resources, allowing native-image to include class metadata.
[thinking] 
[thinking] However, if class bytes aren't on the build classpath, how do tests work? It seems they run on the JVM to create agent metadata, which could help. It makes me think that maybe dynamic class loading is feasible if the class is preloaded. Lastly, it seems like native images might support loading classes using URLClassLoader.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Exploring native image execution**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering whether the dynamic access report for Native Image could be due to the agent at compile time. I shouldn't overthink it, but I need to include the Diktat fixture jar as a resource instead of on the classpath. Since loadClass on JarState's URLClassLoader won't load new classes, I'm pondering if the existing coverage tasks were passed for other reasons. 
[thinking] 
[thinking] Could it be that native image tests only compile and not run? But the user mentioned execution under Native Image, so I'm curious if the test runtime classpath is set up correctly, including generated fixture jars as resources.
[thinking] 
